Dialogs.Dialog: I think Rinko is too close to you.
I know it's a little late for that, but I thought it didn't seem like Rinko.
It's just like you, isn't it？ That means you do what you want to do, right, ▲小早川＊▲？
If you want to be close to me, then that's fine by me, ▲小早川＊▲.
I can't help it, I enjoy being with you.
I really want to be with you much longer.
Every day I say goodbye when it's late... I wish we could have spent more time together.
You know, I actually won a prize. Two days and one night in Atami, ▲小早川＊▲.
Why don't we go there... together？
Are you ready to go home？
I understand the trip... I'll go with you.
I-I see. Well, when do you want to go？
Then. Two days and one night from ▲月▲▲日▲！
Actually, I won it again. Our trip to Atami.
...really？ I think you're secretly buying them.
Wrong！ Well, you know, I was wondering if you wanted to go with me.
Um, the day of the date...
Then. Two days and one night from ▲月▲▲日▲！
I'm going shopping for the trip and I want you to come along. Of course, now.
For the trip？ Well, we've got a lot of stuff to get ready for... Okay, let's go！
You're my senpai in life, so show me the good stuff.
(Wait. We're going on a trip to the beach in the summer...)
Roughly, is this everything we need？
When push comes to shove, I'm counting on you.
"Maybe" not. You and Rinko are in this together.
Thank you for going out with me and helping me.
Just make sure you're prepared ahead of time, okay？
I will take proactive steps for good.
That's unusual for spring. I happened to wake up early.
Good morning. Sorry to keep you waiting.
It's so hot！ Is it cooler over there？
Good morning. I don't think so.
A perfect day for an outing？
It's chilly... If it's cold over there too, I'll be leaving in a heartbeat.
Oh come on, just bear with it a little bit.
Well, I changed it... How do you like it？
That's fine. I don't expect a clever answer.
...don't you think it's a little too late for that.
How do you like my outfit today？
It was Rinko's fault for asking.
Hah, I want to take it off.
What do you think？ Rinko kinda likes this style.
Yes, yes, honesty is the best.
I don't want to speak about personal preferences, but... read the air.
What do you think of today's outfit？
Yeah, for today's trip. Does it look good on me？
Hehe, can you say it more？
You know, with all the travel stuff, I hope you didn't forget.
The transfer is over there. You really haven't done any research.
Since there are two of us, it would be inefficient if we didn't share the workload, right？
(What's the division of labor for you ▲小早川＊▲？)
My little brother, you know, he loves trains.
Oh, I get it. That's the age he's at, isn't it？ Pictures, models, that kind of stuff.
Maybe. You don't get it, ▲小早川＊▲？
It's over there. Did you forget？
I don't forget, or rather, I don't remember in the first place.
Unlike the Shinkansen, it has a certain elegance.
Why the bipolarity？ The right ones are in the right places, right？
You're the one who lost them？
Did I not leave them with you？ With the person who leads us.
Don't make it up. Also, I'm not a leader.
What should we do... Isn't it bad？
Worst case scenario, you might have to pay extra money.
Eh, I feel bad for you...
Don't look at me and say that.
The ticket is down there. Under your girlfriend's seat.
Oh, really. Thank you very much. That was helpful.
(...You're polite to strangers, which is a good thing...)
I heard that Atami used to be a standard honeymoon destination.
...nothing, I just wanted to let you know that I know about it...
So, you know, pretending to be newlyweds for the duration of the trip.
Well, if you don't like it, it's fine.
Why don't you do what you want？
We will be arriving at Atami shortly. Thank you very much for your business today.
Come on, get ready. We're going down.
Since when are you such a regular.
It's okay, it's a place of our memories.
Well, what do we do first？
Well, it's a little early. Let's take a break and have lunch.
It's a nice view, isn't it？ But don't lean on it too much.
Then you won't get near it？ See, don't you want to walk on the railing？
And you didn't even eat potato chips on the train.
I don't eat potato chips on these long trips because it goes against Rinko's policy.
I wonder what it is. Male chauvinism？ Good grief.
Well, I get that kind of impression. What was the story？
It's unfinished because the author died in the middle of it.
Oh, I see. That's what I'd expect from a Library Committee member.
You are one too, you know. But I have a favor to ask you.
I can see the punchline. You're gonna kick me！
That's fine. You can enjoy Atami sightseeing to the fullest for that price.
What kind of tourism scam is that...
I wonder if Rinko's kick can cure you of indigestion.
You want to vent？ Is there an arcade around？
We don't have to come all the way out here to go to the arcade. Well, I haven't seen any.
When I come to a new place, I want to play against the locals.
Wait, wait. You're giving up too soon！
Because I can't see one. I don't understand.
Don't you want to give Rinko a piggyback ride？
Even though you're a healthy high school boy？
I'm not going to do it anymore. I don't have the strength to go anywhere else.
Well, let's stop for the time being.
The upper leaves are turning red. Hah, why don't they just build an escalator？
The air is so much clearer up here. Do you feel that way especially after a workout？
If you don't exercise, I don't think you would understand, ▲小早川＊▲.
Good job. If you can climb the stairs with your girlfriend on your back, that makes you a man.
The leaves are colored beautifully. It was worth all the hard work.
Ah, you're right. However, I'm the one who's changing colors.
Well, do you want to pay your respects, and make a wish？
Yes, we've come all this way.
(I wish my relationship with you develops further, ▲小早川＊▲.)
(I feel like I'm closer to you than before, ▲小早川＊▲！)
I feel like it somehow works. Is it a power spot？
So this is the Sun Beach.
Okay, I'll go change. Wait for me.
(Hmm. Looking around, I still think you are the cutest in this beach, ▲小早川＊▲.)
So this is what summer travel is all about after all？ It's so impromptu.
Well, you know, I did respond to your request for a swimsuit, right？
Yes, you should be honest and thankful.
(I wonder if you put sunscreen for this cases, ▲小早川＊▲.)
We need to put sunscreen on！
Shouldn't you put on some sunscreen, ▲小早川＊▲？
Oh right, I forgot about that.
I have no choice. I'll apply it for you.
Sun Oil？ I see, so you have that kind of hobby.
I bet the wheat-colored skinned you is cute too！ Shall I apply for you, ▲小早川＊▲？
I understand. But don't come closer.
It looks like an artificial beach.
You don't have to be so blunt.
I'm not saying it's a bad thing. There's no rule that says artificial things are inferior to natural things, right？
Yes. What matters is the person next to you at the time, right？
What's with all the cherry blossoms？
So, Towano cherry blossoms are Towano's cherry blossoms？
I don't remember there being such a thing.
I've never heard of it, but it could be used for community development.
Like manjuu or something like that？
Then maybe the tax revenue would increase and the school facilities would be improved, you know？
(That's not correct... I'll better shut up.)
Excuse me, sorry to keep you waiting.
Is that an e-mail？ You've been fiddling with it a lot since a while ago.
What, are you the type that doesn't like it when people touch their phones when they are with you？
Just a little, you know, travel record.
I like it, show it to me later.
(Well, I guess it can't be helped.)
Just a little more time. There's still time, right？
Yes, but... the earlier we get to the hotel, the more time we have together...
Oh, it really is a ropeway.
Are we going to ride this？
Yeah, all the way up there.
That's not true. Come, let's go.
Oh, it's moving. That's pretty fast.
Hey, do you mind if we tweak it？
You don't have to ride this thing to get to the top. You can take a bus or something.
I guess... but this is fun！
Well, yeah... I guess it depends on the passenger, hehe.
They say if you put a lock here, we will both be happy for a long time.
Locks of love at Cape Aijo？
That's what I'm talking about. Let's do it！
You know that is against Rinko's policy, but... I have no choice.
Is the lock you and Rinko put here still around？
It's tough on God, too, with all the love and romance that goes on. I feel like he's doing a good job.
Hey, what about over there？ Aren't we going？
Um... I don't see it on the schedule in particular.
Can I at least get a brochure？
I may have said this before.
Why do couples like high places？
I don't know why. But it's true, we also like high places, don't we？
Yeah. Especially with the night view...
It's time to go to the hotel.
When we arrive, we should rest first.
Yeah, I'm going to sleep. Maybe.
N-nothing... I mean, are you okay with it？
You're staying together. It's the first time.
Are you used to it by now？
A warm welcome to Hotel Onoya.
I have a reservation under the name ▲苗字▲...
Please let me show you to your room.
Please hand me your luggage, ma'am.
Just a thought. Do hotel staff need to carry luggage？
Isn't that a waste of labor？ I can carry it myself.
And what do they mean with lovely？ I'm not a little animal！
(I dare not respond to my wife.)
What's going on with the room？
I thought I took it separately...
They said it was a mistake. There doesn't seem to be any other rooms available, so we are in trouble.
I did not！ I'll go talk to them again.
We can stay in the same room.
Because we came on a trip together. It's weird that we have to stay in separate rooms. I want to be with you.
I don't know, it's just the norm to be in the same room.
What, you like it when we are apart？
That's even worse... that's why I'm holding back.
Haha, that's the first thing you check. I get you.
Tea？ Yes, yes, I'll make you some.
Thank you. Next time, Rinko will make some for you.
Say, would you like to go explore the hotel, ▲小早川＊▲？
Sounds good. Looking for retro games？
So that's what you're after. That's fine, too.
Now if there was a little deserted lounge or something, that would be great, but is there？
Karaoke？ Or, a sauna？ I'm excited about these things.
I'm thirsty. I'm going to buy some juice.
Take care. Don't take a detour. Don't get lost.
Hmm. Massage, 4,500 yen for 40 minutes, huh... Too much for a high school student.
You forgot your wallet. Good grief, you're a child, ▲小早川＊▲.
(Ah, what do I do with the key...)
I'll leave it as it is
Idiot！ Why is the door locked？ Come back quickly！
Sorry, I thought I would find you quickly. You left your wallet, didn't you？
I left with only coins. Hurry up and unlock the door.
What are you wandering around for？
You left your wallet, didn't you？ That's why I chased after you.
Huh？ Of course I took only coins with me.
There's still time before dinner. Let's take a bath first.
Hmm？ This hotel has a variety of baths, and the men and women change according to the time of day.
At this time of the day, the men are the Roman baths and the women are the Flower baths, huh？
I'd prefer a Roman bath, but... it's fine, I don't want to wait.
You know, why don't we do that？
We go to the bathroom together, and after you step out, you wait for me.
Ah, you want to try that？
Why not. Today Rinko feels like trying old customs.
Well, I'll be waiting for you here when I get out.
Oh. It certainly looks like Rome！
(We've done a lot of walking today. Time to relax.)
(I bet you're not ready yet ▲小早川＊▲...)
Did you get all the way up to your shoulders？
Did you count to ten seconds？
Two seconds is enough！ I don't want to be hot.
Well, your yukata looks pretty good on you, doesn't it？
That's because it looks good on you.
I thought you don't like it that much. Somehow.
I'll eat it. Because I'm a cat.
Well, you know, I saw it on the Internet.
There is a place called Hatsushima that can be reached by boat from Atami Port.
They say there is a legendary beach there that no one has ever reached.
When you pledge your love to each other there, they say you will be happy forever... and I'm kind of embarrassed to say it.
Heh, this is the first time I've heard of this.
Maybe I'd like to try going there for sometime.
No one has ever been there, right？ Sounds like it'll be something exciting.
So, should we look for it tomorrow？
Yeah, let's do that. Tomorrow we will go to Hatsushima.
We'll go there. To the legend.
Yeah, it's not exactly a classic.
Yes, let's look for it again...
Oh, there is a ping-pong table here.
Don't be like that. Come on, let's do it.
Yes, yes, I'll do my best.
What are you really trying to do, you idiot.
I sweated even after taking a bath.
Why don't you just go back in？
You can't even get Rinko to take you seriously... you really are an old man, aren't you？
Sounds like a pain in the ass.
(Oh, there is an open-air bath？ Maybe I'll invite you to go there, too, ▲小早川＊▲.)
(I just got in earlier, so I'm done with baths.)
Let's take an open-air bath ▲小早川＊▲！
Open-air bath？ No thanks, it's a hassle.
I see... Then I won't go inside either.
Open-air bath... Heh, that sounds good.
(There's snow on the ground... I didn't even notice it.)
W-wait... what are you yelling at？
Yeah, I didn't notice it at all when it happened.
(It's an open-air bath！ Of course there will be snow.)
What？ Don't be yelling at me.
Eh, yeah... well it's an open-air bath, isn't it？
What's it like over there, ▲小早川＊▲？
Geez, stop it. You don't want people to come in.
Besides！ I can't relax listening to your voice！
They have a private bath... Would you like to try it？
(Private, huh... is that a good idea？)
Really？ Then I'm going in first.
(A private bath is what you call a family bath... what to do？)
What's the matter？ You're not coming in？
What are you looking at？ Lecher.
You were looking at me so hard, you lecher old geezer.
...kidding. Bathing in a swimsuit is pretty nice, isn't it？
(Thank goodness... almost made me look like a pervert.)
Idiot！ Pervert！ What are you thinking！
They'll hear us outside！ I'm going to get out！
(I wonder if you know what you're talking about ▲小早川＊▲.)
(You said something about the night view ▲小早川＊▲...)
Invite her for an evening stroll
(It's already dark. Let's not do this.)
Wanna go for a night walk ▲小早川＊▲？
You know, today, when we looked out over the city, you said something about the night view.
Yes... but I don't want to go, it's a hassle
Got you. Hehe, I remember what I said.
You got me, then you want to go？
A night walk... hehe. Sounds exciting.
It's a little far, but let's walk.
It's not like I imagined... I'm disappointed.
I'm impressed with the night view... but I'm not in character.
That's right, don't dwell on it.
Well, anyway, does that mean you're satisfied？
I see. It's summer and we're at the beach.
I knew it was different from the fireworks in Towano.
That's a given. It's just a different kind of firework...
I can't see in front of me.
I heard that the beach here will be lit up, ▲主人公＊▲.
Heh, the beach？ I wonder what it's like.
Hmm... they say apathy gets old fast.
It's really lit up. This is how it's going to be.
Usual for girls？ You mean that？ Don't think like that.
There are many girls in the world, but your girlfriend is the only one.
Let's go back to the room, ▲小早川＊▲.
(I get it, certainly that's a little nerve-wracking.)
You know... should we turn off the lights now？
But, say... you don't want to sleep yet, right？
Good morning. Did you sleep well last night？
That surprised me. Did you and Rinko oversleep？
...Huh？ My apologies. It seems I had the wrong time.
(I'm glad I woke up early. I got a decent night's sleep last night.)
(I think I'll watch you for a while...)
Hehe, how long are you going to stay in bed？
Oh, good morning... Is there any more decent way to wake me up？
We still have time, don't we？ Can we snuggle？
Listen, I'm going to change, okay？
Rinko doesn't have a propensity for exposition.
I think enough time has passed
Oh, you're done. Let's go out to eat then.
(You were over, so it was okay.)
All right. Let's go out to eat, then.
I knew a hotel breakfast would be a buffet.
Yeah. I don't have to eat anything I don't like.
I mean, you can eat whatever you want, right？
It's the same, huh... how is that the same？
You'll get old if you worry about the details.
This is because you eat while looking the other way.
Hey, can you go get me a replacement？
All right, let's go. Let's get ready to leave.
Today is Hatsushima. The legendary beach, let's see if we can find it.
The legendary beach... I hope we can find it again.
It'll be fine, we will find it.
To get to Hatsushima, we'll take a boat from here.
I hope I don't get tipsy.
Hmm, so this is what it looks like inside.
Then, if I feel like it, too.
Don't force yourself. Why don't you go get excited？
It's not that I'm forcing myself.
Oh, I knew it would feel good.
Birds... They often follow moving boats.
Potato chips again. You won't be able to eat lunch.
Don't worry, they are delicious. Also, I won't give you any.
Yes, yes. Don't spill too much.
Haha, it came for your potato chips.
This is Rinko's... I mean, it's pretty much scarier than that！
It's okay, it seems kind of friendly.
Who！？ They all have the eyes of hunters！
Thanks, I'll give you some potato chips in return.
You're suddenly speaking badly against nature？
I'm not saying it's a bad thing. You think it's bad to be small？ Do you have a problem with Rinko？
It's a good question... But let's eat lunch first.
Do you like it here？ Why？
...well, yeah. But it looks delicious, let's go in.
You came all the way here for ramen. Do you want to eat shrimp？
It's okay because it's Iwanori ramen. But give me some shrimp.
Now, let's see if we can find the legendary beach.
Well, we should just look for it at our pace.
Oh, there's some kind of legend written about it.
It doesn't seem to have anything to do with it.
Can we pay a visit or something？
Heh, you can climb the lighthouse.
There are only a few lighthouses open to the public, or so dad told me.
Wow, your father knows a lot？
I heard he's kind of a lighthouse fanatic. So, do you want to go up there？
Okay, that's fine. I can brag to my dad.
Oh, amazing. You can see in all directions.
Well, let's stay like this for a while.
We couldn't find the Legendary Beach...
We couldn't find it, so it really must be a legend...
Even though I couldn't find the beach, I had a good time. What about you ▲小早川＊▲？
I can hear the sound of waves.
I can hear them. Come, over there.
The beach seems to be around here.
I can also hear the sound of waves...
I thought the beach was around here.
Hah, it's okay. I didn't really want to go there that badly.
Is the legendary beach... around here？
Yes. It's really not on the map.
...it looks more normal than I thought.
You know, the part when you pledge your love for each other.
Rinko Kobayakawa pledges to love you forever.
I, ▲苗字▲ ▲名前▲, also pledge to love Rinko Kobayakawa forever.
We've been together since yesterday, haven't we？
That's because it's a trip for two.
This whole time, my heart was beating fast.
From the time I fell in love with you.
Since that time, I've been so thrilled...
I'm falling more and more in love with you.
I'm afraid of this kind of thing...
But I want to know. I want to know what will happen in the future.
Tell me more about what you like...
This is the place, the legendary beach.
Yes. It's not even on the map.
Rinko Kobayakawa vows to love you, forever.
I, ▲苗字▲ ▲名前▲, also pledge to love Rinko Kobayakawa forever.
What's the matter, we've been together since yesterday.
Yeah, maybe that's a first time for us.
After so much time together, it seems like you should be bored...
I'd like to spend more time with you.
I don't want to let you go.
And yet we have to leave？
I know it can't be helped, but...
This is how I'll hold out for now. But when I grow up...
Yeah... I love you... I want to kiss you.
Right. It's not even on the map.
It was true... It really is so... beautiful.
I told you. This is where we pledge our love.
Rinko Kobayakawa will love you forever.
I, ▲苗字▲ ▲名前▲, also pledge to love Rinko Kobayakawa forever.
This is the first time we have been together like this...
One thing, I've grown up, haven't I？
How much more growning do I need to do？
I thought maybe I wouldn't have to go home.
I'm just happy to be with the one I love.
I love you. Ever since then.
One more time, like that time...
I love you... Do you want to kiss？
Yeah... the place where you and Rinko had memories...
What are you thinking right now？
For Rinko, it was about the first time we came here.
Do you even know what to do after this？
Hmm. I guess the trip is almost over.
I'm saying farewell to the island.
You are indeed tired. Hang in there a little longer.
We have some time before the train arrives.
Do you want to see the souvenirs？
Who are you buying it for？
Won't you bring some to your friends？
I don't have the kind of friendship that can be broken just by not buying souvenirs from a trip.
Could be just trying to be cool, like an excuse...
That's okay. Besides, it's hard to buy souvenirs, isn't it？
You don't need to see it.
That's why I'm not good at it. I'm not confident in my taste in souvenirs.
You think？ I don't want it to hurt.
A tanned version of you ▲小早川＊▲...
I'm tired indeed. I'm going to fall asleep.
You slept too much. We almost didn't make it home.
Sorry about that. But if we're talking about sleeping a lot, ▲小早川＊▲...
Pretend you didn't see that part.
You and Rinko, how long have we been together？
Well, it's roughly a day and a half.
A day and a half for this...
If we stayed longer, you know, what would happen？
Hehe, a secret. But it doesn't sound bad, okay？
Sorry, they sent me a message.
It's okay... hah, so it's over.
You know... I want to go again.
Hah, I guess this is goodbye... Bye-bye.
You're not going home like this, are you？ You forgot something important.
(Going home alone after a trip... feels a little sad.)
Almost at the convenience store, you know.
Hey, can I see your luggage？
Rinko's luggage might have gotten mixed up.
Is it that important？ What is that？
Don't ask me that kind of question.
I could have sent it to you...
(And she's gone. The vibe of the farewell is gone...)
Come on. Huh, aren't we pretending to be newlyweds.
Hmm. Well, this is not so bad.
How could it not be fun？
Because I want to be with you.
Is it so much fun to look at the view？
I'm feeling sleepy... Oh, it's not that I'm bored.
It's spring... you're thinking that, aren't you？ You sound old.
Not too hot, not too cold. That's the best.
I'm cold！ Do something about it.
Is it really impossible to visit everything in one night？
I'm tired... Just a little bit.
I know, I have extensive knowledge about this place. I'm kidding by the way.
I can't believe we've been together this long...
I want to drink some tea.
...what are you looking at？ I don't mind, though.
Come to think of it, it's been a while since I've seen tatami mats.
It's a nice room. I think it's called "Poku".
I brought Valentine's Day chocolates. You know, I'm your girlfriend.
...it's not something to get so excited about. It's just an event.
Well, I'm honestly happy that you gave it to me, ▲小早川＊▲.
Then it would have been worth the trouble of standing in line to buy it...
You even did all that for me.
Well, in addition to my other shopping... it just happened to catch my eye...
I see, thanks. I'll have to get into the spirit of this for White Day, too.
...oh, there's that too. I see, yes. Well then, I'll be waiting.
Oh... you can't pretend to be calm. Rinko can see through it all.
If you have a girlfriend and you don't get it, I would feel sorry for you, wouldn't I？ That's why...
You won't give it to me？
It's a little awkward to just hand it over and tell you "please accept it！" so say "Please give me some chocolate, Rinko-sama！".
...geez, I was kidding！ Okay, here you go.
Today is Valentine's Day. Maybe you thought there are chocolates waiting for you.
Will you give some to me？
That's a given, I'm your girlfriend, you know. Here you have it.
And, so you know, it's handmade. Are you happy？
Handmade？ I see, you did your best...
It was hard work, you know, so make sure you taste it. Hehe.
Yeah. Also... White Day, I'm expecting a lot, okay？
It's your birthday... today. Happy birthday.
...it can't be helped. I'm your girlfriend, after all.
Also, take this, a gift. I don't guarantee you'll like it.
You picked it out for me, didn't you？ I'm sure I'll love it, ▲小早川＊▲.
Today is your birthday, right？ That said, happy birthday.
You can be even more happy. Rinko even went to the trouble of preparing a gift for you.
I'm so out of character, I feel lost. I will not forgive you if you don't thank me.
Thank you so much. You really thought about me, ▲小早川＊▲.
Ah, geez！ Why am I so embarrassed...
Happy Birthday. I wanted to be the first to say it, but has someone already said it？
I see, thanks！ Don't worry you're the first one, ▲小早川＊▲.
I see. What a relief... Oh, Rinko brought you a gift.
Really？ Thank you, I'm so happy.
Rinko is also happy to see your happy face.
Maybe that's why we give gifts, to see that look on the other person's face.
It's your birthday today. Happy birthday.
Oh, and I have a gift for you.
It's fine, don't worry so much.
Lately, I've been thinking. You're always spoiling Rinko, aren't you？
I'm getting all kinds of things, not just gifts...
But Rinko, she can't give you much back because of how she is... honestly, do you still love Rinko？
That's obvious. I know how you feel about me, ▲小早川＊▲.
I see... then I'm happy, I guess.
What's the matter？ You being honest today？
That's just for today, and since it's my birthday, I'll pretend it's special.
